2 nonprofit association or provider of electric service which is
3 declared to be a public utility pursuant to NRS 704.673 and which
4 provides service only to its members; or
5 (2) A municipal electric utility which provides electric
6 service to fewer than 100,000 retail electric meters.
7 (c) “Station power” means energy used on the site of a
8 wholesale generation facility for the operation, maintenance or
9 repair of the facility, including, without limitation, energy used for
10 lighting, thermal regulation, fuel processing and powering
11 equipment. The term:
12 (1) Includes any such load:
13 (I) That is served by a provider of electric service over a
14 distribution line that is connected to the system of the provider of
15 electric service at a point that is separate from the switchyard
16 where a generation or storage resource of the wholesale
17 generation facility is connected to the transmission system; or
18 (II) That is served by the system of a provider of electric
19 service that is connected to the transmission system at the same
20 point as a generation or storage resource of the wholesale
21 generation facility during any period when the generation or
22 storage resource is idle.
23 (2) With respect to a wholesale generation facility which
24 generates electricity from geothermal resources, does not include
25 energy used to operate fans or pumps or parasitic loads associated
26 with the production of electricity from a geothermal resource.
27 (d) “Wholesale generation facility” means a facility for the
28 generation of electricity that has a capacity in excess of 1
29 megawatt and:
30 (1) Is not affiliated through common ownership with an
31 end-use customer that purchases electricity; and
32 (2) Does not provide the electricity generated by the facility
33 directly and exclusively to the end-use customer described in
34 subparagraph (1).
35 Sec. 2. 1. This section becomes effective upon passage and
36 approval.
37 2. Section 1 of this act becomes effective:
38 (a) Upon passage and approval for the purpose of adopting any
39 regulations and performing any other preparatory administrative
40 tasks that are necessary to carry out the provisions of this act; and
41 (b) On January 1, 2026, for all other purposes.
